  "base_commit": "f25fe30a414a5b7bc12a723f44837dbe3d1bc960",
  "pr_number": 2282,
  "issue_number": 2281,
  "issue_title": "Bug: Actual Budget CSV import fails entirely when a row has a blank payee",
  "issue_body": "## Before you start (required)\n\n### General checklist\n\n- [x] I have removed personal / sensitive data from screenshots and logs\n- [x] I have searched [existing issues](https://github.com/we-promise/sure/issues?q=is:issue) and [discussions](https://github.com/we-promise/sure/discussions) to ensure this is not a duplicate issue\n\n### How are you using Sure?\n\n- [x] I am a self-hosted user (local only)\n\n### Self hoster checklist\n\n- Self hosted app commit SHA: reproducible on current `main` (`f25fe30a4`) and on every version since `ActualImport` was introduced in #1830.\n  - [x] I have confirmed that my app's commit is the latest version of Sure\n- Where are you hosting?\n  - [x] Docker Compose\n\n---\n\n## Bug description\n\nImporting an **Actual Budget** transaction CSV fails with a generic \"Import failed\" when the file contains a row with a **blank Payee**. Actual exports such rows for reconciliation balance adjustments and starting balances, e.g.:\n\n```csv\nAccount,Date,Payee,Notes,Category_Group,Category,Amount,Split_Amount,Cleared\naccount1,2026-05-14,,Reconciliation balance adjustment,Income,Income,0.43,0,Reconciled\n```\n\nA single blank-payee row aborts the **entire** import (not just that row). The UI shows only:\n\n> Import failed\n> Please check that your file format, for any errors and that all required fields are filled, then come back and try again.\n\n\u2026and the worker log shows the job completing normally (`ImportJob ... done`) with no error, which makes it hard to diagnose. Selecting only rows that have a payee imports successfully, which is how the blank payee was identified as the trigger.\n\n### Root cause\n\n`ActualImport#generate_rows_from_csv` maps the row name directly from the Payee column with no fallback:\n\n```ruby\n# app/models/actual_import.rb\nname: row[name_col_label].to_s,   # \"Payee\" \u2192 \"\" when blank\n```\n\nThis differs from the base importer and `MintImport`, which both fall back to `default_row_name`:\n\n- `app/models/import.rb`: `name: (csv_value(row, name_col_label, \"name\") || default_row_name).to_s`\n- `app/models/mint_import.rb`: `name: (row[name_col_label] || default_row_name).to_s`\n\n`Entry` requires a name (`app/models/entry.rb`: `validates :date, :name, :amount, :currency, presence: true`). Because `ActualImport#import!` wraps all rows in a single `transaction do ... entry.save! ... end`, the blank name raises `ActiveRecord::RecordInvalid` and rolls back every row. `Import#publish` rescues the error and stores it on `import.error` while marking the import `failed`, so the Sidekiq job exits cleanly and logs `done`.\n\nThe preflight (\"clean your data\") step does not catch this because `ActualImport#required_column_keys` is only `%i[date amount]`, so a blank-payee row is considered valid at preflight but still fails at `entry.save!`.\n\n### To Reproduce\n\n1. Go to **Import** \u2192 **Financial Tools** \u2192 **Import from Actual Budget**.\n2. Paste/upload an Actual CSV that includes at least one row with an empty `Payee` (e.g. a reconciliation balance adjustment or starting-balance row, as shown above).\n3. Apply configuration \u2192 Next through category/account mapping \u2192 **Publish import**.\n4. The import finishes as **Import failed** even though the data is valid; the worker log shows the job as `done` with no visible error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nActual rows with a blank Payee should import successfully (they are valid transactions). A sensible name should be derived \u2014 e.g. fall back to the **Notes** column (which carries text like \"Reconciliation balance adjustment\") and then to the generic default name \u2014 matching the blank-name handling already used by the base importer and `MintImport`. One unusual row should not abort the entire import.\n\n### Proposed fix\n\nIn `ActualImport#generate_rows_from_csv`, fall back to Notes, then to `default_row_name`, when Payee is blank:\n\n```ruby\nname: row[name_col_label].to_s.presence ||\n      row[notes_col_label].to_s.presence ||\n      default_row_name,\n```\n\n### Screenshots and/or recordings\n\nN/A (reproducible from the CSV above).\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-11T07:04:57.000Z",
